quran[75]{c,v,t}:
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,Who created and ЋєperfectlyЋЇ fashioned ЋєallЋЇ
  87,3,and Who ordained precisely and inspired accordingly
  87,4,and Who brings forth ЋєgreenЋЇ pasture
  87,5,then reduces it to withered chaff
  87,6,"We will have you recite Ћєthe Quran, O Prophet,ЋЇ so you will not forget Ћєany of itЋЇ"
  87,7,unless God wills otherwise.¬†He surely knows what is open and what is hidden
  87,8,We will facilitate for you the Way of Ease
  87,9,So ЋєalwaysЋЇ remind Ћєwith the QuranЋЇвАФЋєevenЋЇ if the reminder is beneficial Ћєonly to someЋЇ
  87,10,Those in awe Ћєof GodЋЇ will be mindful Ћєof itЋЇ
  87,11,But it will be shunned by the most wretched
  87,12,who will burn in the greatest Fire
  87,13,where they will not Ћєbe able toЋЇ live or die
  87,14,Successful indeed are those who purify themselves
  87,15,"remember the Name of their Lord, and pray"
  87,16,But you Ћєdeniers onlyЋЇ prefer the life of this world
  87,17,even though the Hereafter is far better and more lasting
  87,18,This is certainly ЋєmentionedЋЇ in the earlier ScripturesвАФ
  87,19,the Scriptures of Abraham and Moses
  88,1,Has the news of the Overwhelming Event reached you ЋєO ProphetЋЇ
  88,2,On that Day ЋєsomeЋЇ faces will be downcast
  88,3,"ЋєtotallyЋЇ overburdened, exhausted"
  88,4,burning in a scorching Fire
  88,5,left to drink from a scalding spring
  88,6,"They will have no food except a foul, thorny shrub"
  88,7,neither nourishing nor satisfying hunger
  88,8,On that Day ЋєotherЋЇ faces will be glowing with bliss
  88,9,ЋєfullyЋЇ pleased with their striving
  88,10,in an elevated Garden
  88,11,where no idle talk will be heard
  88,12,In it will be a running spring
  88,13,along with thrones raised high
  88,14,and cups set at hand
  88,15,and ЋєfineЋЇ cushions lined up
  88,16,and ЋєsplendidЋЇ carpets spread out
  88,17,Do they not ever reflect on camelsвАФhow they were ЋєmasterfullyЋЇ created
  88,18,and the skyвАФhow it was raised ЋєhighЋЇ
  88,19,and the mountainsвАФhow they were firmly set up
  88,20,and the earthвАФhow it was levelled out
  88,21,"So, Ћєcontinue toЋЇ remind Ћєall, O ProphetЋЇ, for your duty is only to remind"
  88,22,You are not ЋєthereЋЇ to compel them Ћєto believeЋЇ
  88,23,"But whoever turns away, persisting in disbelief"
  88,24,then God will inflict upon them the major punishment
  88,25,Surely to Us is their return
  88,26,then surely with Us is their reckoning
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and the ten nights
  89,3,and the even and the odd
  89,4,and the night when it passes
  89,5,Is all this ЋєnotЋЇ a sufficient oath for those who have sense
  89,6,Did you not see how your Lord dealt with вАЩ»ВdвАФ
  89,7,Ћєthe peopleЋЇ of IramвАФwith ЋєtheirЋЇ great stature
  89,8,unmatched in any other land
  89,9,and Tham√їd who carved Ћєtheir homes intoЋЇ the rocks in the ЋєStoneЋЇ Valley
  89,10,and the Pharaoh of mighty structures
  89,11,They all transgressed throughout the land
  89,12,spreading much corruption there
  89,13,So your Lord unleashed on them a scourge of punishment
  89,14,ЋєForЋЇ your Lord is truly vigilant
  89,15,"Now, whenever a human being is tested by their Lord through ЋєHisЋЇ generosity and blessings, they boast, вАЬMy Lord has ЋєdeservedlyЋЇ honoured me!вАЭ"
  89,16,"But when He tests them by limiting their provision, they protest, вАЬMy Lord has ЋєundeservedlyЋЇ humiliated me!вАЭ"
  89,17,"Absolutely not! In fact, you are not ЋєevenЋЇ gracious to the orphan"
  89,18,nor do you urge one another to feed the poor
  89,19,And you devour ЋєothersвАЩЋЇ inheritance greedily
  89,20,and love wealth fervently
  89,21,Enough! When the earth is entirely crushed over and over
  89,22,"and your Lord comes Ћєto judgeЋЇ with angels, rank upon rank"
  89,23,and Hell is brought forth on that DayвАФthis is when every ЋєdisbelievingЋЇ person will remember Ћєtheir own sinsЋЇ. But what is the use of remembering then
  89,24,"They will cry, вАЬI wish I had sent forth Ћєsomething goodЋЇ for my ЋєtrueЋЇ life.вАЭ"
  89,25,"On that Day He will punish ЋєthemЋЇ severely, like no other"
  89,26,"and bind ЋєthemЋЇ tightly, like no other"
  89,27,"ЋєGod will say to the righteous,ЋЇ вАЬO tranquil soul"
  89,28,"Return to your Lord, well pleased Ћєwith HimЋЇ and well pleasing Ћєto HimЋЇ"
  89,29,So join My servants
  89,30,and enter My Paradise.вАЭ